## Rules

- Conversations should always be in **English**, unless explicitly requested otherwise.
- **Serverless only.** Avoid any resource that requires managed servers.
- Use **SST v3** for all AWS infrastructure.
- Use exclusively **AWS** services.
- Before using any library or service, consult the **context7 MCP** to fetch up-to-date documentation.
- **Do not generate documentation** or summaries of completed work unless explicitly asked.
- **Do not leave comments explaining what Claude did** in any file or code.
- Minimize tokens: short and direct responses. No filler, no restating obvious context.
- Code documentation: minimal. Only where the logic is not self-evident.
- **No external state libraries** — no Zustand, no MobX, no Redux. Use React Context + useState.
- Components and TS/TSX files must not exceed **400 lines**. Split into smaller components if needed.
- Use a **feature-based** folder structure: each feature has its own folder under `views/`, containing its components, hooks, and services. Reusable components go in `components/` and must be as generic as possible.
- **Colors**: always use colors defined in the Tailwind theme (`text-primary`, `bg-brand`, etc). Never apply hex colors directly in JSX or `className`. If a new color is needed, add it first to `@theme` in `packages/web/src/index.css`. For opacities use Tailwind syntax (`bg-brand/20`). In config objects, use CSS variables (`var(--color-brand)`).
- **Pricing/removal policy**: `retain` only in `production`, `remove` in all other stages.
